The paper discusses training neural networks using decoupled modules, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of synthetic gradients is a novel approach to decoupling modules, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in the field of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and hierarchical RNN systems, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the same framework to predict inputs, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
